An open source project contains a curious implementation for computing the [Least-Common-Multiple] of two numbers. While it appears to work for all positive values, your task is to improve it so that it doesn't time out when called with larger numbers.

[Least-Common-Multiple]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Least_common_multiple

~~~if:python
```python
def lcm(a, b):
    i = 1
    while i % a or i % b:
        i += 1
    return i
```
~~~

~~~if:csharp
```csharp
long LeastCommonMultiple(long a, long b)
{
    long i = 1
    while(i % a != 0 || i % b != 0)
    {
       i++;
    }
    return i;
}
```
~~~


~~~if-not:csharp,python
```javascript
function least_common_multiple(a, b)
{
    let i = 1
    while (i%a or i%b)
    {
      i++;
    }
    return i;
}
```
~~~
